• requiring Verizon to dedicate significant cash flow from operations to the payment of principal,

 interest and other amounts payable on  our  debt,  which  would  reduce  the  funds  we  have  available  for  other  purposes,  such  as  working  capital,  capital  expenditures, dividend payments and acquisitions;

• making it more difficult or expensive for Verizon to obtain any necessary future financing for working capital,

